: \"LG Electronics (Thailand) Co., Ltd., in collaboration with Mo Sys and the world class partner, offers a complete virtual\",\n          \"language\": \"th\"\n        },\n        \"page_content\": \"\\n\\n\\n\\n\\nLG partners with mo-sys, empowering thai talents in production industry and | RYT9\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\u0e15\\u0e48\\u0e32\\u0e07\\u0e1b\\u0e23\\u0e30\\u0e40\\u0e17\\u0e28\\n\\u0e40\\u0e28\\u0e23\\u0e29\\u0e10\\u0e01\\u0e34\\u0e08\\n\\u0e2b\\u0e38\\u0e49\\u0e19-\\u0e01\\u0e32\\u0e23\\u0e40\\u0e07\\u0e34\\u0e19\\n\\u0e01\\u0e32\\u0e23\\u0e40\\u0e21\\u0e37\\u0e2d\\u0e07\\n\\u0e40\\u0e17\\u0e04\\u0e42\\u0e19\\u0e42\\u0e25\\u0e22\\u0e35\\n\\n\\r\\n          \\u0e2d\\u0e37\\u0e48\\u0e19 \\u0e46\\r\\n        \\n\\n\\u0e1a\\u0e31\\u0e19\\u0e40\\u0e17\\u0e34\\u0e07\\n\\u0e2d\\u0e2a\\u0e31\\u0e07\\u0e2b\\u0e32\\n\\u0e17\\u0e31\\u0e48\\u0e27\\u0e44\\u0e1b\\n\\u0e22\\u0e32\\u0e19\\u0e22\\u0e19\\u0e15\\u0e4c\\n\\u0e17\\u0e48\\u0e2d\\u0e07\\u0e40\\u0e17\\u0e35\\u0e48\\u0e22\\u0e27\\n\\u0e01\\u0e35\\u0e2c\\u0e32\\nEnglish\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n        LG partners with mo-sys, empowering thai talents in production industry and corporate customers to create world-class content with cutting-edge tech at mo-sys academy bangkok      \\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\nFacebook\\n\\n\\nTwitter\\n\\n\\nLine\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\nTechnology News\\n            Tuesday July 16, 2024 08:41            \\u2014PRESS RELEASE LOCAL\\n\\n\\n\\nLG Electronics (Thailand) Co., Ltd., in collaboration with Mo-Sys and the world-class partner, offers a complete virtual production solution featuring LED virtual sets, high-performance cameras for film, live broadcast, sports, and world-class studio and film set lighting. This comprehensive offering is available at Mo-Sys Academy Bangkok, a cutting-edge production studio and training center providing expertise in virtual production for film, television, advertising, and other forms of media. The academy boasts state-of-the-art technology, including XR, AR, and VR solutions used in live events and concerts, as well as equipment for producing films and TV series. Mo-Sys Academy Bangkok is also equipped with the most advanced and comprehensive virtual production technology in Asia Pacific, empowering creators to produce world-class content.\\nMs. Jeerapa Kongswangwongsa, VP of Business Solutions and Head of Enterprise, LG Electronics (Thailand), Co., Ltd., said: \\\"LG has partnered with key partners Mo-Sys and Thairath Group to launch the state-of-the-art virtual production studio that aims to empower Thai professionals in production industry by providing access to cutting-edge equipment and facilities, enabling them to create high-quality content that meets global standards. At this studio, we have installed our LED Signage screens (model LBAE026), the Digital Floor screen (model LFCG039), and the latest LED display, LG MAGNIT (model LBAF015). The LG MAGNIT is a Micro LED display that delivers ultimate realism with its 1.56 mm pixel pitch, and a frame rate of up to120 Hz in a size of 2.4 x 2 meters. These installations, valued at over 60 million baht, replace traditional green screens, delivering more realistic pictures, eliminating the need for complex post-production work, and significantly reducing time and cost expenditures. This studio also offers high-quality tools and solutions from our leading partners, readily available for media production professionals to utilize in crafting their masterpieces.\\\"\\nMs. Yupapak Tawanna, VP of APAC region, Mo-Sys, explained about the world-class innovations in this studio: \\\"Since its introduction, Mo-Sys Academy Bangkok has been utilized for a variety of high-quality media productions, including live events, broadcasts, films, commercials, music videos, and more, bringing quality content to the public eyes. We are delighted to assist Thai production professionals by providing accessible and efficient filming and editing tools, enabling them to create realistic, high-quality productions with affordable cost. Our solutions are trusted by world-class content production partners, demonstrating our commitment to excellence. Currently, this studio also provides training in virtual production using XR, AR, and VR technologies for live events, concerts, and other content production. Progressive solutions like In-Camera Visual Effects (ICVFX) and Cinematic Focus technologies for producing movies, short films, dramas, and TV series are also included in our training. As a global leader in virtual production solutions, Mo-Sys will work with our networks in London and Los Angeles to bring in new cutting-edge technologies, making them accessible to media production personnel in Thailand and empowering them to create high-quality content. All these initiatives aim to propel the Thai media production industry to be able to compete at an international level.\\\"\\nMo-Sys Academy Bangkok Studio offers a wide range of virtual production solutions for media production professionals, including high-performance cameras by Canon, the Cinema EOS C400 and RF mount cinema lenses - the CN7x17 KAS T/R1 (17-120mm), specifically designed for In-Camera Visual Effects (ICVFX) compatible. This technology utilizes real-time transmission of CV metadata from cameras and lenses to software, enabling more streamlined workflows, reducing production time, and seamlessly synchronizing live-action footage with virtual screens for exceptional realism. In addition, the studio provides world-class lighting solutions from Aputure, catering to diverse content production needs.\\nThose interested in training courses or utilizing the virtual production solutions at Mo-Sys Academy Bangkok studio can inquire for more information by emailing academy@mo-sys.com or info@mo-sys.com. More information about LG commercial displays can be explored at https://b2bmkt.lge.com/PR_News2024. For more information, please contact the LG Call Center on tel. 0-2057-5757, and keep up with LG news and activities via Facebook fan page: LG Global, and Instagram: lg_thailand.\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n              Latest Technology News            \\n\\n\\n11:52\\n                  Safeguarding Privacy with Synthetic Data                  \\n\\n16 Jul\\n                  LG partners with mo-sys, empowering thai talents in production industry and corporate customers to create world-class content with cutting-edge tech at mo-sys academy bangkok                  \\n\\n15 Jul\\n                  MSC arranged At the Edge of IBM Innovate Secure Insights Optimize                  \\n\\n15 Jul\\n                  KX Venture Capital and AI Fund announce Strategic Partnership to Build AI Startups                  \\n\\n15 Jul\\n                  Huawei Brings Cutting-Edge Technology and Intensive Courses Supporting UTCC towards 'AI Integrated University                  \\n\\n12 Jul\\n                  G-Able Leverages Workday to Enhance HR Efficiencies and Drive Organisational Agility                  \\n\\n10 Jul\\n                  \\\"depa\\\" Opens 3rd Round of Applications for Community Groups and Technicians to Join the 1 Tambon 1 Digital (Chumchon Drone Jai) Project                  \\n\\n10 Jul\\n                  How Technology is Changing the Game for Sports Forever:  Better Efficiency, Engagement, Sustainability and Inclusivity Can Be Expected                  \\n\\n10 Jul\\n                  SCBX, SCB 10X AND SAMBANOVA ENTER INTO MILESTONE AGREEMENT TO EXPAND AI MODELS; TYPHOON THAI LLM ADDED TO SAMBA-1                  \\n\\n9 Jul\\n                  depa Announces Successful Establishment of the First Phase's 35 Drone Repair Centers, a Main Driver for Thailand's Agricultural Drone Ecosystem                  \\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\nCopyright \\u00a9 2007-2024      Dataxet Limited (\\u0e1a\\u0e23\\