0\\n\\n\\uce7c\\ub7fc\\n\\uae30\\uace0\\n\\uc778\\ud130\\ubdf0\\n\\n\\n\\n\\uc54c\\ub9bc\\n\\n\\uc54c\\ub9bd\\ub2c8\\ub2e4\\n\\uc778\\uc0ac\\n\\ubd80\\uc74c\\n\\uc0c8\\ub85c\\ub098\\uc654\\uc5b4\\uc694\\n\\n\\n\\n\\ub9c8\\uc18c\\ucf54\\ub529\\n\\n\\ucf54\\ub529\\n\\uc5d0\\ub4c0\\ud14c\\ud06c\\n\\ucef4\\ud4e8\\ud305\\u00b7AI\\n\\ud14c\\ud06c\\ub9ac\\ud3ec\\ud2b8\\n\\n\\n\\nGLOBAL\\n\\uae30\\ud68d\\u00b7\\uc5f0\\uc7ac\\n\\uc18d\\ubcf4\\n\\ubc31\\uacfc\\uc0ac\\uc804\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\uc18d\\ubcf4\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\uae30\\uc5c5\\n\\n\\n\\uc77c\\ubc18\\n\\n\\n\\ubaa8\\ubc14\\uc77c\\u00b7\\uac00\\uc804\\n\\n\\n\\ubc29\\uc1a1\\u00b7\\ud1b5\\uc2e0\\n\\n\\n\\ubc18\\ub3c4\\uccb4\\u00b7\\ub514\\uc2a4\\ud50c\\ub808\\uc774\\n\\n\\nSW\\u00b7\\ubcf4\\uc548\\n\\n\\n\\uc911\\uacf5\\uc5c5\\u00b7\\uc5d0\\ub108\\uc9c0\\n\\n\\n\\uc18c\\ubd80\\uc7a5\\u00b7\\uc2a4\\ud0c0\\ud2b8\\uc5c5\\n\\n\\n\\uc720\\ud1b5\\u00b7\\uc1fc\\ud551\\n\\n\\n\\ud504\\ub86d\\ud14c\\ud06c\\u00b7\\ubd80\\ub3d9\\uc0b0\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\ubaa8\\ube4c\\ub9ac\\ud2f0\\n\\n\\n\\uc790\\ub3d9\\ucc28\\u00b7\\ubaa8\\ube4c\\ub9ac\\ud2f0\\n\\n\\n\\ub85c\\ubd07\\u00b7\\ub4dc\\ub860\\u00b7\\ud56d\\uacf5\\n\\n\\n\\ubc29\\uc0b0\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\uac8c\\uc784\\u00b7\\ucf58\\ud150\\uce20\\n\\n\\n\\uac8c\\uc784\\u00b7\\uc778\\ud130\\ub137\\n\\n\\n\\uba54\\ud0c0\\ubc84\\uc2a4\\u00b7VR\\n\\n\\n\\ud0a4\\ub35c\\ud2b8\\n\\n\\n\\ubbf8\\ub514\\uc5b4\\u00b7\\uc5d4\\ud130\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\uacfc\\ud559\\u00b7\\ud5ec\\uc2a4\\n\\n\\n\\uacfc\\ud559\\u00b7\\uc6b0\\uc8fc\\n\\n\\n\\uc758\\ud559\\u00b7\\uc815\\ucc45\\n\\n\\n\\uc81c\\uc57d\\u00b7\\ubc14\\uc774\\uc624\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\ud30c\\uc774\\ub0b8\\uc2a4\\n\\n\\n\\uae08\\uc735\\n\\n\\n\\uc99d\\uad8c\\n\\n\\n\\ud540\\ud14c\\ud06c\\u00b7\\ube14\\ub85d\\uccb4\\uc778\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\uce7c\\ub7fc\\u00b7\\uc778\\ud130\\ubdf0\\n\\n\\n\\uce7c\\ub7fc\\n\\n\\n\\uae30\\uace0\\n\\n\\n\\uc778\\ud130\\ubdf0\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\ub9c8\\uc18c\\ucf54\\ub529\\n\\n\\n\\ucf54\\ub529\\n\\n\\n\\uc5d0\\ub4c0\\ud14c\\ud06c\\n\\n\\n\\ucef4\\ud4e8\\ud305\\u00b7AI\\n\\n\\n\\ud14c\\ud06c\\ub9ac\\ud3ec\\ud2b8\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\uc54c\\ub9bc\\n\\n\\n\\uc54c\\ub9bd\\ub2c8\\ub2e4\\n\\n\\n\\uc778\\uc0ac\\n\\n\\n\\ubd80\\uc74c\\n\\n\\n\\uc0c8\\ub85c\\ub098\\uc654\\uc5b4\\uc694\\n\\n\\n\\n\\nGLOBAL\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\nGLOBAL\\n\\n\\nFascinating and Useful Hovering Hologram [Inho's Startup Pick]\\nInterview with Yang Chang-jun, CEO of Marketon\\n\\n\\n\\uae30\\uc790\\uba85\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\tinho\\t\\t\\t\\n\\uc785\\ub825 2024.07.11 10:28\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\nSNS \\uae30\\uc0ac\\ubcf4\\ub0b4\\uae30\\n\\n\\ud398\\uc774\\uc2a4\\ubd81(\\uc73c)\\ub85c \\uae30\\uc0ac\\ubcf4\\ub0b4\\uae30\\n\\n\\n\\ud2b8\\uc704\\ud130(\\uc73c)\\ub85c \\uae30\\uc0ac\\ubcf4\\ub0b4\\uae30\\n\\n\\n\\uce74\\uce74\\uc624\\ud1a1(\\uc73c)\\ub85c \\uae30\\uc0ac\\ubcf4\\ub0b4\\uae30\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\uac00\\n\\uac00\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\uc774 \\uae30\\uc0ac\\ub97c \\uacf5\\uc720\\ud569\\ub2c8\\ub2e4\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\ud398\\uc774\\uc2a4\\ubd81(\\uc73c)\\ub85c \\uae30\\uc0ac\\ubcf4\\ub0b4\\uae30\\n\\n\\n\\ud2b8\\uc704\\ud130(\\uc73c)\\ub85c \\uae30\\uc0ac\\ubcf4\\ub0b4\\uae30\\n\\n\\n\\uce74\\uce74\\uc624\\ud1a1(\\uc73c)\\ub85c \\uae30\\uc0ac\\ubcf4\\ub0b4\\uae30\\n\\n\\nURL\\ubcf5\\uc0ac(\\uc73c)\\ub85c \\uae30\\uc0ac\\ubcf4\\ub0b4\\uae30\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\ub2eb\\uae30\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\nTo view something using electronic devices, an output device like a monitor is needed. Even smartphones display content through an LCD screen. Holograms, on the other hand, project objects into mid-air instead of on a screen. These holograms often appear in movies depicting near-future technology, like Marvel's \\\"Iron Man\\\". In these films, hand gestures in the air move and interact with holograms. In reality, holograms use light reflection and refraction, making it difficult to fully implement them in mid-air.\\nMarketon is a startup researching and developing devices that can project holograms in mid-air, even in bright environments. Unlike augmented reality (AR) or virtual reality (VR) which require separate display devices (HMDs), Marketon's technology displays a monitor screen visible to the naked eye in mid-air.\\nMarketon calls this \\\"hovering hologram\\\". Just as smartphones are operated by touch gestures, hovering holograms can be controlled by touching the air. IT Chosun met with Yang Chang-jun, CEO of Marketon, to discuss the motivation behind developing hovering holograms and their vision.\\n\\n\\nYang Chang-jun, CEO of Marketon / IT Chosun\\n\\n\\n\\nStarted as Contactless Display During COVID-19 Pandemic\\n\\nYang Chang-jun founded Marketon in October 2019. He explains that Marketon's initial business direction was not to create hovering hologram devices as it is now. Initially, given Yang's 20 years of experience at the Korea Association for ICT Promotion, Marketon planned to focus on related services and consulting. The turning point in Marketon's business direction was the COVID-19 pandemic that began in early 2020.\\nYang said, \\\"In early 2020, there were rumors about COVID-19 infections from elevators in the Gasan Digital Complex area. Since everyone was wearing masks, people thought elevator buttons were the medium of infection. I thought we could solve this with IT technology. So we created a contactless device where pressing a virtual button floating in the air would be like pressing the actual elevator button.\\\"\\nThis contactless elevator button device evolved into the hovering hologram that Marketon is currently developing. The key feature of the hovering hologram is that it doesn't require a separate display device. It projects light reflected from a mirror into mid-air through special glass. A sensor that recognizes hand position is added to enable touch operation. From the side, it looks like gesturing in the air, but from the front, it appears as if you're touching and operating an actual screen.\\n\\n\\nDemonstrating the Marketon hovering hologram device. / IT Chosun\\n\\n\\n\\nHologram Display Overcoming AR/VR Limitations\\n\\nThis also addresses the device penetration problem, which is considered a barrier to AR/VR popularization. For example, VR device developers like Apple, Meta (Oculus), HTC VIVE, and VR content creators are trying to expand the ecosystem.\\nHowever, VR devices worn on the head can be heavy or need to be connected to charging cables, making it difficult to fully enjoy virtual spaces. VR device prices are also as high as a high-spec PC or more. They're expensive and inconvenient. In contrast, hovering holograms can be operated by hand gestures on a screen floating in mid-air. Without wearing any separate VR equipment, operations like surgical simulations are possible with the naked eye.\\nYang emphasizes that Marketon's hovering hologram is the technology closest to digital holograms. Holograms are divided into analog and digital holograms. Analog holograms typically refer to technology that shows different images depending on the viewing angle. They are mainly used in toys or souvenirs like lenticular prints.\\nOn the other hand, digital holograms are the technology seen in SF creations like Iron Man or Star Wars. Realistically, it's still a technology in the research stage that hasn't been commercialized yet. Current holograms include pyramid holograms that project light into a closed space like a box, propeller holograms that split light using propellers, and theater-style holograms that project light in dark spaces. All three are fixed holograms that are difficult to interact with.\\nYang confidently states, \\\"Marketon's hovering hologram can be seen with the naked eye without any additional devices and can be interacted with by hand. I believe Marketon's hovering hologram technology is the closest to digital hologram technology.\\\"\\n\\n\\nRunning an anatomical practice simulation in a classroom with Marketon's hovering hologram device installed.\\u00a0/ Marketon\\n\\n\\n\\nGoal: Develop Mobile Hologram Device Within 4 Years\\n\\nMarketon's hovering hologram devices are currently being adopted in museums and exhibitions. Instead of docents or signposts explaining exhibits, visitors can directly rotate and view 3D modeled exhibits through the hovering hologram. Yang explains that anything that can be seen on a computer can be output as a hovering hologram.\\nYang plans to pursue slimming down the hovering hologram device and expanding its applications in the future. Currently, Marketon's device is thick due to the mirror angle. This is analyzed to be similar to the process of CRT monitors for PCs and CRT TVs, which had large backs, becoming thin like current LCD monitors or OLED TVs.\\nIn fact, Marketon's devices are pursuing slimming in a similar way. If slimming is achieved, it would be possible to place Marketon's device on top of a smartphone screen and operate the smartphone screen as a hologram floating in the air.\\nExpanding the applications of hovering holograms is also linked to discovering Marketon's revenue structure. Hovering holograms are interesting but not essential technology. The same scenes can be viewed with existing display devices.\\nTherefore, Marketon's hovering holograms are currently mainly used as devices to provide special experiences in event spaces like museums or exhibitions. Marketon is researching ways to expand applications, along with lightening and slimming, to find out where and how hovering holograms can be used in various ways.\\nYang says, \\\"Hovering holograms, when viewed from the side, don't show properly, like a monitor with a privacy film attached, but can be seen with the naked eye without any medium to output the screen. It can also play roles like hand recognition double security devices as seen in movies, so it can be widely used not only in museums and schools but also in places like finance.\\\"\\nHe added, \\\"By incorporating AI, we can create digital humans that answer various questions from different angles, and if we implement mobile hologram devices, holographic video calls or meetings would be possible. Our goal is to continuously reduce the thickness of the device and develop a mobile hologram device that generates holograms on smartphones within 4 years.\\\"\\ninho@\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\uae30\\uc790\\uc758 \\uc804\\uccb4\\uae30\\uc0ac\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\uc800\\uc791\\uad8c\\uc790 \\u00a9 IT\\uc870\\uc120 \\ubb34\\ub2e8\\uc804\\uc7ac \\ubc0f \\uc7ac\\ubc30\\ud3ec \\uae08\\uc9c0\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n \\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\uac1c\\uc758 \\ub313\\uae00\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\ud68c\\uc6d0\\ub85c\\uadf8\\uc778\\n\\n\\ub313\\uae00 \\ub0b4\\uc6a9\\uc785\\ub825\\n\\n\\n\\n0 / 400\\n\\ub4f1\\ub85d\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\ub313\\uae00 \\uc815\\ub82c\\n\\n\\ucd5c\\uc2e0\\uc21c\\n\\ucd94\\ucc9c\\uc21c\\n\\ub2f5\\uae00\\uc21c\\n\\n\\n BEST\\ub313\\uae00\\n\\nBEST \\ub313\\uae00\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\ub2f5\\uae00\\uacfc \\ucd94\\ucc9c\\uc218\\ub97c \\ud569\\uc0b0\\ud558\\uc5ec \\uc790\\ub3d9\\uc73c\\ub85c \\ub178\\ucd9c\\ub429\\ub2c8\\ub2e4.\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\ub2eb\\uae30\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\ub354\\ubcf4\\uae30\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\ub313\\uae00\\uc0ad\\uc81c\\n\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\uc0ad\\uc81c\\ud55c \\ub313\\uae00\\uc740 \\ub2e4\\uc2dc \\ubcf5\\uad6c\\ud560 \\uc218 \\uc5c6\\uc2b5\\ub2c8\\ub2e4.\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\uadf8\\ub798\\ub3c4 \\uc0ad\\uc81c\\ud558\\uc2dc\\uaca0\\uc2b5\\ub2c8\\uae4c?\\r\\n\\t\\t\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\ube44\\ubc00\\ubc88\\ud638\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\u00a0\\uc0ad\\uc81c\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\ub2eb\\uae30\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\ub313\\uae00\\uc218\\uc815\\n\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\ub313\\uae00 \\uc218\\uc815\\uc740 \\uc791\\uc131 \\ud6c4 1\\ubd84\\ub0b4\\uc5d0\\ub9cc \\uac00\\ub2a5\\ud569\\ub2c8\\ub2e4.\\r\\n\\t\\t\\n\\n\\n\\n\