p\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\nFind us on Facebook\\n\\nThe Washington Times\\nOpinion\\nLocal\\nSports\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\nFind us on X\\n\\n\\n\\nThe Washington Times\\nOpinion\\nLocal\\nSports\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\nSubscribe\\nClassifieds\\nE-edition\\nCustomer Service\\nCareers\\nTerms\\nPrivacy\\nRSS\\nAdvertise\\nFAQ\\nAbout\\nContact\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\nAll site contents \\u00a9 Copyright 2024\\u00a0The Washington Times, LLC | 3600 New York Avenue NE | Washington, DC 20002 | 202-636-3000\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\",\n        \"type\": \"Document\"\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"lc\": 1,\n      \"type\": \"constructor\",\n      \"id\": [\n        \"langchain\",\n        \"schema\",\n        \"document\",\n        \"Document\"\n      ],\n      \"kwargs\": {\n        \"metadata\": {\n          \"source\": \"https://www.nytimes.com/2024/07/12/world/asia/india-ambani-wedding-billionaire.html\",\n          \"title\": \"Ambani Wedding Shows Off India\\u2019s New Gilded Age - The New York Times\",\n          \"description\": \"Many Indians cheer the rise of moguls like Mukesh Ambani, whose son\\u2019s wedding has become a global spectacle. To them, India\\u2019s poverty is predictable, but such opulence is not.\",\n          \"language\": \"en\"\n        },\n        \"page_content\": \"\\n\\n\\n\\nAmbani Wedding Shows Off India\\u2019s New Gilded Age - The New York Times\\n  \\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\nSkip to contentSkip to site indexAsia Pacific\\u00a0Today\\u2019s PaperAsia Pacific|A Wedding Puts India\\u2019s Gilded Age on Lavish Displayhttps://www.nytimes.com/2024/07/12/world/asia/india-ambani-wedding-billionaire.htmlShare full article217AdvertisementSKIP ADVERTISEMENTYou have a preview view of this article while we are checking your access. When we have confirmed access, the full article content will load.Supported bySKIP ADVERTISEMENTA Wedding Puts India\\u2019s Gilded Age on Lavish DisplayMany Indians cheer the rise of moguls like Mukesh Ambani, whose son\\u2019s wedding has become a global spectacle. To them, India\\u2019s poverty is predictable, but such opulence is not.Listen to this article \\u00b7 8:13 min Learn moreShare full article217Anant Ambani, son of Indian businessman Mukesh Ambani, and his fianc\\u00e9e, Radhika Merchant, during a wedding welcome ceremony in Mumbai earlier this month.Credit...Ashish Vaishnav/SOPA Images, via LightRocket, via Getty ImagesBy Anupreeta DasReporting from New DelhiJuly 12, 2024Leer en espa\\u00f1olThe younger son of Mukesh Ambani, India\\u2019s richest man, is set to wed his fianc\\u00e9e in Mumbai on Friday, the finale of a monthslong extravaganza that signaled the arrival of the unapologetic Indian billionaire on the global stage \\u2014 and introduced the world to the country\\u2019s Gilded Age.For much of the year, the festivities surrounding the nuptials of Anant Ambani and Radhika Merchant, the daughter of a fellow business tycoon, have grabbed eyeballs for their lavish displays of wealth. Millions have been spent on diamonds and emeralds the size of credit cards, on haute couture saris, on wedding invitations made of silver and gold.Billionaire businessmen, Bollywood stars, models and politicians were among the more than 1,200 guests at a pre-wedding bash in March. Bill Gates stopped by. Rihanna performed. In May, the bride and groom-to-be threw a four-day party on a luxury cruise ship in the Mediterranean; Ms. Merchant told Vogue India they couldn\\u2019t find a land venue big enough to host all their guests.Jay Gatsby would have been awed.The spectacle has served as an invitation to peek inside India\\u2019s uppermost echelons, where a few individuals and families have amassed astounding fortunes in recent years. Buoyed by booming growth and a cheerleading government, the number and wealth of Indian billionaires has soared. They are overlords of the Indian economy, running the phone networks that connect millions of people, the hospitals that treat them, the supermarkets where they shop and the high-rises in which many live.ImageThe pop star Rihanna performed for guests at the pre-wedding celebrations of Anant and Radhika in Jamnagar, Gujarat, in March.Credit...Reliance Industries, via ReutersA lot of money, in the hands of the few.In 2000, India had nine billionaires, according to Oxfam. Now, India has 200 billionaires, who collectively hold around $1 trillion in wealth, according to Forbes \\u2014 nearly a quarter of the country\\u2019s 2023 gross domestic product.We are having trouble retrieving the article content.Please enable JavaScript in your browser settings.Thank you for your patience while we verify access. If you are in Reader mode please exit and\\u00a0log into\\u00a0your Times account, or\\u00a0subscribe\\u00a0for all of The Times.Thank you for your patience while we verify access.Already a subscriber?\\u00a0Log in.Want all of The Times?\\u00a0Subscribe.AdvertisementSKIP ADVERTISEMENTSite IndexSite Information Navigation\\u00a9\\u00a02024\\u00a0The New York Times CompanyNYTCoContact UsAccessibilityWork with usAdvertiseT Brand StudioYour Ad ChoicesPrivacy PolicyTerms of ServiceTerms of SaleSite MapCanadaInternationalHelpSubscriptionsManage Privacy Preferences\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\",\n        \"type\": \"Document\"\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"lc\": 1,\n      \"type\": \"constructor\",\n      \"id\": [\n        \"langchain\",\n        \"schema\",\n        \"document\",\n        \"Document\"\n      ],\n      \"kwargs\": {\n        \"metadata\": {\n          \"source\": \"https://thatoregonlife.com/2024/07/mr-bills-village-smokehouse/\",\n          \"title\": \"Few People Know The Best Jerky Ever Is Hiding At Mr. Bill's Village Smokehouse\",\n          \"description\": \"This spot might just become your new favorite place to stop off on the Oregon coast.\",\n          \"language\": \"en-US\"\n        },\n        \"page_content\": \"\\n\\n\\n\\nFew People Know The Best Jerky Ever Is Hiding At Mr. Bill's Village Smokehouse\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n \\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\nNews\\nRegions + Cities\\nAdventures\\nLodging\\nFood & Drink\\nShop\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n \\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\nFew People Know The Best Jerky Ever Is Hiding In This Oregon Coastal Town by Jessica Tomlinson | Jul 10, 2024 | Featured, Food, Food & Drink, Interesting, Lincoln City, Oregon Coast, Travel\\n\\n\\n\\nShare This Article\\nIf you're like me and love beef jerky, smoked salmon and other delicious smoked meats, there's a spot you can't miss when you head out to the Oregon coast. Mr. Bill's Village Smokehouse is a treasure trove of smoked meats and seafood bursting with rich, smoky flavor. We all have our favorite spots to stop off for salt water taffy, seafood and other goodies on the coast, and this one might just become your new favorite!\\nLegendary Flavors At Mr. Bill's Village Smokehouse In Lincoln City, Oregon\\nPhoto by Jennifer Morris via Google Local.\\nWhether you\\u2019re a local or just passing through Lincoln City, Mr. Bill's is a can't miss. The Yelp reviews really don't do this place justice. Freshly smoked jerky, thick and meaty salmon full of flavor, and smoked oyster sticks that are insanely good are just a few of the delights waiting for you when you stop by.\\nPeppered smoked salmon. Photo by Kris P. via Yelp.\\nLike salmon? Take one bite of the alder smoked king salmon at Mr. Bill's and you'll understand why it's a local favorite. This specialty is crafted using wild Alaskan King Salmon, brined in a brown sugar and salt cure. Naturally smoked to a moist, flaky perfection, it\\u2019s a treat that your taste buds will thank you for.\\nPhoto by Mr. Bill's Smokehouse Facebook page.\\nI absolutely love beef jerky, and Mr. Bill's has some of the best, not only on the Oregon coast, but in the entire state. There are several kinds of alder smoked jerky to try, from sweet and hot to savory.\\nBeef jerky. Photo by Robyn W. via Yelp.\\nLooking for something a little sweet? The teriyaki beef jerky is Mr. Bill's most popular choice. This jerky offers a delightful blend of sweet and savory flavors. We also recommend the Cajun jerky for something different, and the sweet-heat jerky for those that love to have a little spice in their life.\\nPhoto by Alexa Escobar' via Google Local.\\nFor a unique twist on a classic, try the teriyaki alder smoked oyster sticks. These oysters are infused with teriyaki sauce before being smoked, resulting in a sweet and savory delicacy that seafood lovers won't be able to get enough of.\\nPhoto by S. West via Google Local.\\nBeyond jerky, plain smoked oysters and salmon, Mr. Bill's also offers an enticing range of other smoked seafood, including alder smoked Albacore tuna, fresh caught alder smoked Alaskan halibut with brown sugar and a salt cure, and habanero alder smoked oyster sticks. Delicious!\\nPhoto by Mr. Bill's Smokehouse Facebook page.\\nTip: Don\\u2019t Miss the Baked Beans! These delicious baked beans are another local favorite and include pieces of Mr. Bill's mouthwatering smoked brisket. They're delicious and add a perfect side to any of the smoked treats.\\nPlease Note: All of the items from this smokehouse must be refrigerated.\\nMr. Bill's Village Smokehouse Information\\nPhoto by Jana Patterson via Google Local.\\n\\nLocation: 2981 US-101, in Lincoln City, Oregon.\\nHours: 9 AM - 5 PM, seven days a week.\\nGet more information and current prices at the Mr. Bill's Smokehouse website.\\n\\nCheck out other awesome things to do in Lincoln City with our guide.\\n\\nMr. Bill's Village Smokehouse stands as a shining example of local businesses that we love in Oregon. If you\\u2019ve got a favorite spot or business in mind, don\\u2019t hesitate to nominate them\\u2014they might just be highlighted in an upcoming feature for That Oregon Life. Be sure to stay connected with That Oregon Life on Facebook and Instagram to stay up to date on remarkable destinations, attractions, and happenings in the Beaver State.\\nShare This Article\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\u2190 Oregon's Bigfoot Museum Boasts the Largest Collection of Bigfoot Artifacts Worldwide\\n\\n\\n\\n\\nUnraveling the Mystery: Bigfoot Sightings and Encounters in Oregon \\u2192\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\nWritten By Jessica Tomlinson\\nJessica Tomlinson is a native Oregonian currently living in Southern Oregon. She has been blogging since 2006. She loves nature, photography, hiking, camping, and exploring Oregon's wilds.\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\nRelated Articles\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\nInjured 160lbs Great Pyrenees Rescued from Saddle Mountain on Oregon Coast \\n\\nby Tyler James | Jul 16, 2024 | News, Oregon CoastIn a dramatic and heartfelt rescue on July 12, a 160-pound Great Pyrenees was carried off Saddle Mountain after its paws became severely injured during a hike. The incident has sparked conversations about the safety and preparedness of hiking with pets on rough...\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\nThis Popular Oregon Caf\\u00e9 Is Famous for a Sweet Roll That Will Make Your Taste Buds Explode \\n\\nby Jessica Tomlinson | Jul 16, 2024 | Bend, Central Oregon, Featured, Food, Food & Drink, Interesting, Restaurants, TravelTheir hand rolled croissants, rustic and imperfect in the best way, have a unique character that\\u2019s hard to find elsewhere.\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\nDramatic Footage Captures Heroic Police in Oregon Saving Family from Burning Home \\n\\nby Tyler James | Jul 12, 2024 | Central Oregon, NewsIn a dram