ier LeagueEFLChampions LeagueChampionshipLeague OneLeague TwoCloseFootballEuro 2024Watch epic moment The Killers give fans goosebumps with Mr Brightside as they live stream England win\\nLee DaveyPublished: 10:23, 11 Jul 2024Updated: 11:43, 11 Jul 2024Lee DaveyPublished: Invalid Date, Fans celebrated wildly after The Killers paused their London gig to watch the final moments of England's win over the Netherlands.The US rock band followed the closing minutes of the game before launching into their huge hit song \\u2018Mr Brightside\\u2019 to the jubilation of 20,000 fans packed into the O2 Arena.3The closing stages of the semi-final were beamed on the screen at the O2 Arena on Wednesday nightCredit: @Rhevolver\\nFans were quick to post the footage on social media in what was described as a 'goosebump' moment that even saw the band become embroiled in the celebrations.With England seconds away from booking their place in Sunday\\u2019s final, the lights were turned down and the TV commentary was blasted out over the speakers with the game beamed onto the screen behind the stage.At the final whistle, the crowd erupted as red and white streamers were fired from the stage.The band then topped it off by playing the hit song Mr Brightside, creating a moment fans in attendance will never forget. \\\"Tonight we played for England,\\\" the group's Twitter account later posted.Read more Euros Watkins reveals crazy prediction with Palmer before dramatic England winner in Euros semi 'Disgraceful' - Ex-England stars say they were lucky to get penalty against NetherlandsOllie Watkins\\u2019 added-time winner booked England\\u2019s spot in the Euro 2024 final against Spain in Berlin.The Three Lions put in their best display of the tournament after falling behind after just six minutes thanks to a superb strike from Xavi Simons.Gareth Southgate\\u2019s men hit back through Harry Kane\\u2019s penalty and were unlucky not to lead at the interval when Phil Foden\\u2019s brilliant curler struck the post.A tense second half which was arguably shaded by the Dutch, saw both sides have chances to win the game. After Bukayo Saka saw his effort ruled out for office, substitute Watkins made no mistake to fire England into a second-successive European Championship final.Watkins had played just 20 minutes of football for England before his entrance in Dortmund and admitted that despite a lack of game time, he felt he could make an impact if handed his chance.Most read in Euro 2024 Morata reminds Rodri as he sings about Gibraltar and now the FA are taking action 'Stop it' - Shearer interrupts Lineker to shut down suggestion of Southgate replacement Two England stars make this Euro 2024 best XI as Chelsea and Liverpool told to get excited The potential candidates to replace Southgate as manager steps down from England duty3Ollie Watkins' superb late goal sent England to the Euro 2024 final3Fans at the O2 Arena erupted at the final whistleCredit: @Rhevolver\\n\\u201cI\\u2019ve been waiting for that moment for weeks,\\u201d Watkins told ITV. \\u201cIt\\u2019s taken a lot of hard work to get to where I am today. I\\u2019m delighted.\\u201cI swear on my life that I said to Cole Palmer that he\\u2019s going to set me up today and I\\u2019m going to score. It\\u2019s the best feeling ever.\\u201cI\\u2019m lost for words, really,\\u201d Watkins continued. \\u201cWhen you score there are emotions that come through your body but this is a different feeling.\\u201cIt was slow motion when I was running over to the boys and celebrating.\\u201cI said to Cole we were both going to get on the pitch and he was going to set me up at half-time. It happened. I manifested it.Read More on talkSPORT Lamine Yamal makes social media blunder just moments after Spain Euro 2024 win Kane gets 1/10 with Walker and Southgate slammed as England suffer more Euros heartbreak\\u201cAs soon as he turned I knew to make the move. You don\\u2019t get that opportunity very often. I had to be greedy.\\u201cI\\u2019ve seen it go in the bottom corner. I don\\u2019t think I\\u2019ve hit the ball that sweet before in such a special moment.\\u201dJason Cundy and Jamie O'Hara lose their minds as Ollie Watkins scores the winner to send England to the Euro 2024 finaltalkSPORT will bring you live commentary of the Euro 2024 final on Sunday as England bid to make history against Spain. Tune in via the website or the app, and follow our live Euro 2024 blog for all the build-up.TopicsEuro 2024England FootballYOU MIGHT LIKERECOMMENDED FOR YOUMORE FOR YOUMost Read Yoro to become fifth most expensive teenager ever as he flies in for Man United medicalShareLive Blog Yoro travels for Man United medical, Real Madrid chase Alexander-Arnold, Diaby latestShare Newcastle boss Howe would consider England offer as FA looks for Southgate replacementsShare Morata reminds Rodri as he sings about Gibraltar and now the FA are taking actionShareFOLLOW talkSPORTServicesDownload talkSPORT AppSign up to talkSPORT BETHow to listenSign outTopics A-ZContact preferenceContact usAdvertise on talkSPORTWork for usNews UKLicense contentCookie SettingsLink Your AlexaThis service is provided on talkSPORT Ltd's Terms of Use in accordance with our Privacy Policy.\\n\",\n        \"type\": \"Document\"\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"lc\": 1,\n      \"type\": \"constructor\",\n      \"id\": [\n        \"langchain\",\n        \"schema\",\n        \"document\",\n        \"Document\"\n      ],\n      \"kwargs\": {\n        \"metadata\": {\n          \"source\": \"https://narrabricourier.com.au/2024/07/11/pride-of-the-lions-on-display-as-club-supports-local-youth/\",\n          \"title\": \"Pride of the Lions on display as club supports local youth - The Courier\",\n          \"language\": \"en-AU\"\n        },\n        \"page_content\": \"\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\nPride of the Lions on display as club supports local youth - The Courier\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\nClose\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\nHOMENEWSSPORTSUBSCRIBE/LOGINSOCIALBUSINESSCOMMENT\\u25bcEDITORIALYOUR SAYTHUMBS UP AND DOWNCARTOONTOPICALCLASSIFIEDSFEATURES\\u25bcANNUAL REVIEW 2019BUSINESS AWARDSHEALTH AND WELLBEINGNorth WestStateNationalBOGGABRIREAL ESTATEWEE WAAPAGES FROM THE PASTCONTACTBOOKMARKED \\n\\n\\n\\nSearch for:\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\nJuly 17, 2024 \\n\\n17/7/24 \\n\\nSubscribe\\n\\nSubscriptions\\nLogin\\n\\n\\nAccount\\n\\nSubscription\\nLogout\\n\\n\\n \\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n \\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\nHome\\nNews\\nSport\\nSocial\\nBusiness\\nComment\\n\\nEditorial\\nYour Say\\nThumbs Up and Down\\nCartoon\\nTopical\\n\\n\\nWee Waa\\nBoggabri\\nReal Estate\\nFeatures\\n\\nEducation Guide 2024\\nNarrabri Rugby Club 60th anniversary\\nStud Cattle Sales 2024\\nThe Courier Annual Review 2023\\nEducation Guide 2023\\nCoronation of King Charles\\nWomen in Business 2023\\nPAGES FROM THE PAST: 1920s\\nAnnual Review 2022\\nEducation Guide 2022\\nWomen in Business 2022\\nAnnual Review 2021\\nMADD MONTH 2021\\nBURSARIES AND SCHOLARSHIPS 2021\\nAG & INDUSTRY 2021\\nEducation Guide 2021\\nJoin In 2021\\nEDUCATION GUIDE 2020\\nANNUAL REVIEW 2020\\nIndustrial Feature 2020\\nJoin In 2020\\nNarrabri West 2020\\nHEALTH & WELLBEING 2020\\nAnnual Review 2019\\nEAT STREET 2019\\nBusiness Awards\\nHealth and Wellbeing\\nPages from the Past\\n\\n\\nClassifieds\\nMORE\\n\\nNorth West\\nState\\nNational\\n\\n\\n \\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\nSelect Page\\n\\n\\n\\n \\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\nLions Club of Wee Waa Pride of the Lions on display as club supports local youth\\n\\n\\n \\n\\nA highlight of the Lions Club changeover night was a $500 cheque presentation by Lions president Rob Downey to Christian \\u2018Chippy\\u2019 Petersen, who is the founder of a new initiative RiverBank Youth Works. The beaming smile on Mr Petersen\\u2019s face expressed his deep gratitude for the Lions Club\\u2019s kind donation and support. There will be a further report about RiverBank Youth Works in a future edition. \\n\\n\\n\\nJul 11, 2024\\n\\n \\n\\n\\nWee Waa Lions Club members met at The Imperial Hotel on June 25 for their annual changeover dinner.\\nPresident Rob Downey, who will continue in the top job for another year, warmly welcomed guests and reflected on the club\\u2019s outstanding achievements over the last 12 months.\\nIt\\u2019s clear the Lions Club volunteers play a pivotal role in making the Cotton Capital tick, offering help at a variety of community events and assisting all ages \\u2013 from the debutante ball to Senior Citizens luncheon \\u2013 clocking up an impressive 910 hours of community service in 12 months and making $3910 worth of donations in the 2023/24 period.\\nA highlight of the night was a $500 cheque presentation by Mr Downey to Christian \\u2018Chippy\\u2019 Petersen, who is the founder of a new youth initiative.\\nThe beaming smile on Mr Petersen\\u2019s face expressed his deep gratitude for the Lions Club\\u2019s kind donation and encouragement. There will be a further report about RiverBank Youth Works in a future edition.\\n\\u201cThere are young people in our town who are increasingly finding themselves disengaged with traditional education and making choices that have devastating consequences for them, their families and throughout our wider community,\\u201d said Mr Petersen.\\n\\u201cPrimarily, RiverBank will be about these young people, assisting them to make decisions that will help increase the likelihood of them finding employment, staying out of prison, and achieving success in their lives.\\u201d\\nRiverbank is one of many local initiatives the Lions Club has backed, offering a helping hand where possible to make the town thrive.\\nMr Downey\\u2019s president\\u2019s report for 2023/24 detailed local groups and initiatives Lions members assisted including the pony club gymkhana, Cubbaroo Polocrosse Carnival, Wee Waa Show, Cotton Seed Distributors\\u2019 Awards night, chocolate wheel at the St Joseph\\u2019s Primary School fete, Wee Waa High School formal, town Christmas Tree, Mardi Gras Christmas carnival, Seniors\\u2019 Week, Men\\u2019s Shed, Karinga Village, cake stall for Sh*tbox Rally, debutante ball, PCYC, Youth of the Year, and Anzac Day.\\nDigging deep and rallying hard, Lions made donations to the Christmas Lights Competition, Lions Drug Awareness, Lions Eye Health Programme, Lions Prostate Cancer\\nResearch, Lions Cord Blood Foundation, Ronald McDonald House, Childhood Cancer Mater Foundation, Cancer Council, WWHS, Wee Waa Public School, St Joseph\\u2019s, Namoi Valley Christian School, Wee Waa Show Society, and Wee Waa Arts and Cultural Centre.\\n\\u201cI would like to thank all Lions for their efforts with our projects over the last 12 months,\\u201d said Mr Downey.\\n\\u201cWe welcomed four new members into our club \\u2013 Greg and Denise Robinson, Matt and Tegan Copelin.\\n\\u201cThey have been very involved with our club activities for the year.\\n\\u201cOur sympathy goes out to Kevin and Carmel for the loss of their daughter, Pauline.\\u201d\\nMr Downey also praised those who stepped up to help with the deb ball, giving a special mention to Annette Holland and Kerry Crutcher.\\n\\u201cWe now know how much work Connie Smith puts in,\\u201d he said.\\nThe Lions members had a welcome and youthful boost at the changeover dinner, with Wee Waa Rotaract members attending. They said it was a good social opportunity and the active young club members said they believed the key to success involves local groups supporting each other.\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\nFacebookTweetEmail To order photos from this page click here \\n\\nTHERE'S MORETO THIS STORY\\nGet unlimited access for only $7 per month.\\nSubscribe\\nAlready a subscriber?\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\nAbout The Author\\n\\n\\n\\n \\n\\nAli Smith\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\nLeave a comment Cancel replyYour email address will not be published. Required fields are marked *COMMENTName * \\nEmail * \\nThis site is protected by reCAPTCHA and the Google Privacy Policy and Terms of Service apply.The reCAPTCHA verification period has expired. Please reload the page. \\n\\n \\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\nMore Posts\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n \\nfamily reunion \\n\\nReunion held for Price family descendants\\n\\n\\n\\n\\nThe descendants of the Price family held a family reunion on the June long weekend in Narrabri. Ronald and Elsie Price were married in Nyngan in 1921 and they had 10 children. Triplets George, Stan and Milton arrived six weeks early on December 20, 1921. George was raised by aunties and grandparents as Elsie was unable to cope with the three children. Peter was born in 1923, Mary 1925, Dot 1927, Garnet 1930, Bill 1934 and twins Kevin and John 1937. Ronald was on the family farm at Trangie, however, the family moved to Wee Waa and the property \\u2018Nyora\\u2019 [\\u2026]\\n\\n\\nJul 15, 2024 \\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n \\nPride of Workmanship \\n\\nFour finalists for Rotary Club\\u2019s Pride of Workmanship Award\\n\\n\\n\\n\\nFour finalists have been announced for the Rotary Club of Narrabri\\u2019s annual Pride of Workmanship Award. The accolade celebrates pride in work and specifically, the Pride of Workmanship theme \\u2018Do it once, do it well\\u2019. This year, the award experienced a high calibre of entries, with nominees from a wide range of industries and institutions across the Narrabri Shire community. Following a lengthy adjudication process, the panel of judges named Eden Rozendaal (KR Property), Jay Baquiran (C&D Electronics), Kristy Fuller (Nurruby Children\\u2019s Services) and Lucinda Richards (University of Sydney) as four finalists for the award. President of the Rotary Club [\\u2026]\\n\\n\\nJul 11, 2024 \\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n \\nRiverBank Youth Works \\n\\nChippy\\u2019s light bulb moment set to brighten young lives\\n\\n\\n\\n\\nIn 2018, Christian \\u2018Chippy\\u2019 Petersen had what he called \\u2018a light bulb moment\\u2019 while he was watching a documentary about the BackTrack Youth Works Program established in Armidale. The program\\u2019s founder Bernie Shakeshaft was named the 2020 Australian Local Hero for his outstanding role with the community-led organisation and for turning around the lives of some of the country\\u2019s most vulnerable kids. After seeing the plight of disadvantaged youth in his community, Bernie decided to take action. Starting in 2006 with a shed and an idea, Bernie used the skills he developed growing up and as a jackaroo in the [\\u2026]\\n\\n\\nJul 11, 2024 \\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\nYou have 5/ 5 free articles left this month.\\nTo access all articles Subscribe or Login\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\nGET IN TOUCHTelephone 02 6792 1011\\nEditorial [email\\u00a0protected]Advertising [email\\u00a0protected]Sales [email\\u00a0protected]Classifieds [email\\u00a0protected]Administration [email\\u00a0protected]\\n60 Maitland Street, Narrabri, NSW, 2390\\n\\n\\n\\nABOUT USCONTACT USADVERTISE WITH USCLASSIFIEDS ADVERTISINGSUBSCRIPTIONSPHOTO SALESPRINTING SERVICES\\n\\n\\n\\nPRIVACY POLICYCOMPLAINTS POLICYTERMS OF USE\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\u00a9 2024 North Western Courier Pty Ltd\\n\\n\\n\\nWebsite by TIEMENS CR\\u018eATIVE\\n\\n\\n\\n \\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\",\n        \"type\": \"Document\"\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"lc\": 1,\n      \"type\": \"constructor\",\n      \"id\": [\n        \"langchain\",\n        \"schema\",\n        \"document\",\n        \"Document\"\n      ],\n      \"kwargs\": {\n        \"metadata\": {\n          \"source\": \"https://www.deccanchronicle.com/nation/wagh-nakh-used-by-shivaji-to-be-on-display-in-satara-from-19-july-1809739\",\n          \"title\": \"\\u2019Wagh Nakh\\u201d Used by Shivaji to Be on Display in Satara From 19 July\",\n          \"description\": \"Mumbai: Amidst the growing controversy over wagh nakh (tiger claw-shaped weapon) used by Chhatrapati Shivaji Maharaj to kill Mughal general Afzal Khan, Maharashtra minister Sudhir Mungantiwar on...\",\n          \"language\": \"en\"\n        },\n        \"page_content\": \"\\u2019Wagh Nakh\\u201d Used by Shivaji to Be on Display in Satara From 19 July            Top   ,          e-PaperCorporate Insolvency Resolution Process HomeFact CheckSouthAndhra PradeshTelanganaTamil NaduKarnatakaKeralaNationArunachal PradeshAssamBiharChhatisgarhGoaGujaratHaryanaHimachal PradeshJammu and KashmirJharkhandMadhya PradeshMaharashtraManipurMeghalayaMizoramNagalandOdishaPunjabRajasthanSikkimTripuraUttar PradeshUttarakhandWest BengalWorldSportsCricketFootballTennisOthersEntertainmentTollywoodBollywoodSandalwoodKollywoodMollywoodHollywoodMovie ReviewsTelevisionMusicTheatreOTTGalleryVideosOpinion and EditorialsColumnsDC CommentsBusinessTechnologyEducationSunday ChronicleHyderabad ChronicleIn FocusLifestyleJobsSpecial StoryEditor PickFeaturedScienceAstroguide Fact CheckSouthAndhra PradeshTelanganaTamil NaduKarnatkaKeralaNationArunachal PradeshAssamBiharChhatisgarhGoaGujaratHaryanaHimachal PradeshJammu and KashmirJharkhandMadhya PradeshMaharashtraManipurMeghalayaMizoramNagalandOdishaPunjabRajasthanSikkimTripuraUttar PradeshUttarakhandWest BengalWorldSportsCricketFootballTennisOther NewsEntertainmentTollywoodBollywoodSandalwoodKollywoodMollywoodHollywoodMovie ReviewsTelevisionMusicTheatreOTTOpinion and EditorialsDC CommentsColumnsGalleryVideosBusinessTechnologyEducationSunday ChronicleHyderabad ChronicleLifestyleJobsEditor PickSpecial StoryFeaturedScienceHome \\u00bb Nation\\u2019Wagh Nakh\\u201d Used by Shivaji to Be on Display in Satara From 19 JulyNation DC Correspondent11 July 2024 4:23 PM GMT xWagh nakh (tiger claw-shaped weapon) is used by Chhatrapati Shivaji. (Image: Facebook0Mumbai: Amidst the growing controversy over wagh nakh (tiger claw-shaped weapon) used by Chhatrapati Shivaji Maharaj to kill Mughal general Afzal Khan, Maharashtra minister Sudhir Mungantiwar on Thursday reiterated that the historic weapon was indeed used by the Maratha king. He denied the claims made by historian Indrajit Sawant that the Victoria and Albert Museum in London has said there is no evidence the wagh nakh (in its possession) belongs to Chhatrapati Shivaji Maharaj.Making a statement in the legislative assembly on Thursday, Mr. Mungantiwar said, \\u201cThe government decided to bring wagh nakh after \\u201cShiv Premi\\u201d (devotees of Shivaji) made the demand. We also received documents and records from them insisting that wagh nakh used by Shivaji Maharaj to kill Afzan Khan in 1659 were in the London Museum. We wrote letters to Prime Minister Narendra Modi, the UK PM and the museum clearly stating that we wish to bring wagh nakh used by Shivaji Maharaj to India. We received a response from the museum, which specified that wagh nakh in their possession were used by Shivaji Maharaj against Mughal general.\\u201dMr. Sawant has claimed that the Victoria and Albert Museum has said there is no evidence the wagh nakh (in its possession) belongs to Chhatrapati Shivaji Maharaj. He has also alleged that the state government is bringing the historic weapon on a loan agreement of Rs 30 crore for three years.Responding to Mr. Sawant\\u2019s claim, the minister said, \\u201cThe museum has never said that.\\u201d He also denied that the government is spending Rs 30 crore. He informed the House that the total expenses were Rs. 14.08 lakh including the travel expenses and signing of the agreement. \\u201cThe wagh nakh will be kept on display at the government museum in Satara in the presence of the descendants of the warrior king on July 19,\\u201d he said.( Source : Deccan Chronicle with agency inputs )Wagh Nakhe (tiger claws)\\u00a0chhatrapati shivaji maharaj\\u00a0sudhir mungantiwar\\u00a0Rest of India\\u00a0Maharashtra\\u00a0Mumbai (Bombay)\\u00a0About the AuthorDC CorrespondentLatest News   Next StoryX\",\n        \"type\": \"Document\"\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"lc\": 1,\n      \"type\": \"constructor\",\n      \"id\": [\n        \"langchain\",\n        \"schema\",\n        \"document\",\n        \"Document\"\n      ],\n      \"kwargs\": {\n        \"metadata\": {\n          \"source\": \"https://baodanang.vn/english/culture-sport/202407/diff-2024-finale-expects-thrilling-competition-between-china-and-finland-3977855/\",\n          \"title\": \"DIFF 2024 finale expects thrilling competition between China and Finland - Da Nang English- News - eNewspaper\",\n          \"description\": \"China's Liuyang Lingduan New-art Display Co, and Finland's Joho Pyro Professional Fireworks AB will compete at the finale of ...\\n\\n  Da Nang English- News - eNewspaper\",\n          \"language\": \"vi\"\n        },\n        \"page_content\": \"\\n\\n\\nDIFF 2024 finale expects thrilling competition between China and Finland - Da Nang English- News - eNewspaper\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n272\\n5879\\n1041\\nCulture - Sports\\nculture-sport\\n/culture-sport/\\n1450003\\nDIFF 2024 finale expects thrilling competition between China and Finland\\n1\\nArticle\\n\\nnull\\n\\n\\n\\n.\\nCulture - Sports\\n\\nDIFF 2024 finale expects thrilling competition between China and Finland\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\tBy DA NANG Today / DA NANG Today\\n\\t\\t\\t\\tJuly      11, 2024, 12:03 [GMT+7]China's Liuyang Lingduan New-art Display Co, and Finland's Joho Pyro Professional Fireworks AB will compete at the finale of the Da Nang International Fireworks Festival (DIFF) 2024 themed \\\"Made of Young Generation\\\" on the evening of July 13. They promise to bring to people and tourists the most exciting finale of DIFF seasons.\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\nDespite the hot weather, both Chinese and Finnish teams have been working hard to prepare for the final night. IN PHOTO: The fireworks team from China is installing fireworks at the yard. Photo: THU HA\\n\\n\\n\\nThe competition is equal in talent and strength\\nCurrently, the preparatory works for the forthcoming grand finale by the two fireworks teams have been basically completed.\\nMr. Johan Dan Erik Hollaender, leader of the Finnish fireworks team, revealed that his team will adhere to the general theme of DIFF 2024 \\\"Made in Unity - Global Connection - Radiant Five Continents\\u201d.\\n\\u201cWe are determined to bring an explosive and impressive performance with the overwhelming red colour of fireworks. With the theme of \\\"Made of Young Generation\\\", we want to bring to the audience a performance prepared from the team's heart, mixed with many different emotions and the most positive energy\\u201d he added.\\nThe Finnish fireworks team will continue to show their inherent style in their display in the qualifying round. In the technical part, the team will demonstrate from many different angles including high-altitude, low-altitude, and on the water surface. As for music, they will take the audience through many levels of emotions with different musical works and then will conclude the performance with the hope that everyone will live in happiness and peace.\\n\\u201cWe have been working very hard to design displays of different types of fireworks with lots of different effects. By using about 10,000 firecrackers of all kinds, the team are determined to bring a show that is more perfect and impressive than the previous one\\u201d Mr. Johan Dan Erik Hollaender shared.\\nMeanwhile, members of the fireworks team from China are all diligently preparing for their performance in the grand finale.\\nMr. Liang Weiming, leader of the Liuyang Jingduan New-art Display Co fireworks team from China, couldn't hide his joy after his team entered the finale at their debut at the DIFF. Therefore, the whole team was very excited to plan carefully and confidently for the upcoming performance night. At the finale, the team will bring a difference in their performance by combining Eastern and Western music to draw the audience's attention.\\nThe leader of the Chinese fireworks team voiced his hope that the careful combination of music and fireworks promised to bring the most wonderful moments to the audience.\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\nFireworks team members from Finland are preparing for their performance in the final competition night. Photo: THU HA\\n\\n\\n\\nTeams\\u2019 commitment to return to Da Nang\\nAccording to Mr. Hollaender, the final night of DIFF 2024 will be a competition of equal talent and strength between the two teams.\\n\\u201cIt is difficult to predict the final results because of two different performance styles. However, I think that the two teams are the winners and most importantly, they bring very satisfying and impressive fireworks shows to the audience in Da Nang\\\" Mr. Johan Dan Erik Hollaender said.\\nHaving attended many DIFFs, Mr. Johan Dan Erik Hollaender always feels very comfortable when coming to Da Nang. He shared that he was always full of surprises at the larger scale and professionalism of the festival whenever he returned to the central coastal city.\\n\\u201cWe hope the festival will always maintain its quality and develop more each year. If we have the opportunity, we still want to come back and try to bring different performances to the audience in Da Nang\\\" he expressed.\\nSharing the same opinion, Mr. Liang Weiming highly appreciated the scale of DIFF 2024 as well as the quality of the participating teams. He underlined that his team had great experiences at DIFF 2024. He also affirmed that the warm welcome of the organisers and local people was the motivation for the team members to prepare their best for the final night. \\u201cIf we are given the opportunity, we will continue to return to DIFF\\u201d he noted.\\nMs. Nadia Shakira Wong, the Director of Global 2000 Company, the consulting unit for DIFF 2024, said that all preparations for the finale have been being carried out very well. She added the final competition night was really a challenge for the Finnish and Chinese teams because they only had two weeks to design and prepare for their shows instead of four months in the qualifying rounds.\\nMs. Nadia Shakira Wong further informed that DIFF was increasingly growing stronger and attracted the attention of fireworks teams around the world. The fireworks teams highly appreciated and wanted to participate in the festival whilst the audience did not know which night to choose to watch because every performance night was amazing.\\n\\u201cIt is very difficult to judge which team is stronger than the other because the Chinese and Finnish teams are both very excellent. Every team has a different style and they shine in their own way. The team has strengths in music, and the other has a very beautiful performance design. This causes many difficulties for the judges in scoring and choosing the best team. But I believe, the jury will find the best element of the 2024 DIFF season\\u201d Ms. Nadia Shakira Wong emphasised.\\nReporting by THU HA, VAN HOANG - Translating by M.DUNG, T. TUNG.Other newsDai Binh \\\"Living Museum\\\" - A place to preserve Quang Nam's ancient cultural beauty (10/07/2024)195th death anniversary of mandarin Thoai Ngoc Hau celebrated in Da Nang (10/07/2024)Pickleball, new sport for young people in Da Nang (09/07/2024)Extra's journey - neither easy nor hard (08/07/2024)Good imprint of second Da Nang Asian Film Festival (08/07/2024)Golden era of film narrators (07/07/2024)Talk show in Da Nang spreads values \\u200b\\u200bin director Dang Nhat Minh's films (05/07/2024)2nd Da Nang Asian Film Festival concludes successfully (07/07/2024)9th Viet Nam - Japan Festival 2024 kicked off in Da Nang (05/07/2024)Seminar boosts sharing, connection between Viet Nam and France cinema (04/07/2024).... \\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\",\n        \"type\": \"Document\"\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"lc\": 1,\n      \"type\": \"constructor\",\n      \"id\": [\n        \"langchain\",\n        \"schema\",\n        \"document\",\n        \"Document\"\n      ],\n      \"kwargs\": {\n        \"metadata\": {\n          \"source\": \"https://www.sunshinecoastnews.com.au/2024/07/12/green-light-for-palmer-to-build-biggest-car-museum/\",\n          \"title\": \"Green light for Palmer to build biggest car museum\",\n          \"language\": \"en-AU\"\n        },\n        \"page_content\": \"\\n\\n\\n  \\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\nGreen light for Palmer to build biggest car museum\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n \\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\nHome\\nNews\\n\\nSport\\n\\n\\nOpinion\\n\\nLetters\\n\\n\\nLifestyle\\nProperty\\nLearning\\nCouncil\\nBusiness\\nCommunity\\n\\nGallery\\n\\n\\nSubscribe\\n \\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\nSearch\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\nSunshine Coast News \\n\\n\\n\\n \\n\\n\\nHome\\n\\nSubscribe\\n\\n \\n\\n\\n\\n\\n100% Locally Owned, Independent and Free \\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n \\n\\n\\n\\n  \\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\nSunshine Coast News \\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\nHome\\nNews\\n\\nSport\\n\\n\\nOpinion\\n\\nLetters\\n\\n\\nLifestyle\\nProperty\\nLearning\\nCouncil\\nBusiness\\nCommunity\\n\\nGallery\\n\\n\\nSubscribe\\n\\nSearch \\n\\n\\n\\n\\n \\n\\n\\nHome\\n\\nSubscribe\\n\\n \\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n100% Locally Owned, Independent and Free \\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\nHome\\nNews\\n\\nSport\\n\\n\\nOpinion\\n\\nLetters\\n\\n\\nLifestyle\\nProperty\\nLearning\\nCouncil\\nBusiness\\nCommunity\\n\\nGallery\\n\\n\\nSubscribe\\n\\nSearch \\n\\n\\n\\n \\n\\n\\nHome\\n\\nSubscribe\\n\\n  \\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\nHomeNews\\n\\nMining magnate receives approval to build Australia's biggest car museum\\u00a0\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\nClive Palmer has approval for his latest unexpected venture. Picture: Shutterstock.\\n\\n\\n\\nBy AAP\\n\\n12 July 2024 \\n\\nNews\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\nDo you have a news tip? Click here to send to our news team.\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n \\n\\n\\n\\nNews\\nNew building doubles city centre\\u2019s residential capacity\\nThe Maroochydore city centre will soon be home to about 300 more residents, after the opening of a two-tower development.\\n\\nThe Corso Residential Apartments, by More\\n\\nMore\\n\\n\\n\\nSunshine Coast News -  17 July 2024 0 \\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n \\n\\n\\n\\nNews\\nGroup calls for mass changes at camping hotspot\\nA group of government, tourism and environment representatives has called for widespread changes to improve management of a booming camping destination.\\n\\nThe Teewah and Cooloola More\\n\\nMore\\n\\n\\n\\nSunshine Coast News -  16 July 2024 0 \\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n \\n\\n\\n\\nLocal\\nNew boardwalk opens along Coastal Pathway\\nA 160m section of beachfront boardwalk has opened to the public after nine months of construction.\\n\\nThe Caloundra Headland boardwalk, near Kings Beach, has replaced More\\n\\nMore\\n\\n\\n\\nSunshine Coast News -  16 July 2024 0 \\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n \\n\\n\\n\\nLocal\\nBoy, 11, dies after collision between bike and bus\\nAn 11-year-old boy has died following a bus crash in Buderim this afternoon.\\n\\nPreliminary inquiries indicate a bus was travelling along Jingellic Drive near Karawatha More\\n\\nMore\\n\\n\\n\\nSunshine Coast News -  16 July 2024 0 \\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n \\n\\n\\n\\nBusiness\\nUltimate field trip inspires students to consider further study\\nTwo Sunshine Coast Year 12 students have seen where tertiary education can take them during the field trip of their lives, thanks to the More\\n\\nMore\\n\\n\\n\\nSunshine Coast News -  16 July 2024 0 \\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n \\n\\n\\n\\nNews\\nGlamping retreat and century-old homestead for sale\\nA 20-hectare property with glamping sites and a 100-year-old homestead has hit the market.\\n\\nKanimbia estate, at 27 Innalls Road at Obi Obi, has attracted More\\n\\nMore\\n\\n\\n\\nSteele Taylor -  16 July 2024 0 \\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\nThere\\u2019s been Titanic II, even an A-League club.\\nAnd who can forget Jeff, the ill-fated animatronic Tyrannosaurus rex?\\nNow colourful billionaire Clive Palmer has approval for his latest unexpected venture \\u2013 Australia\\u2019s biggest car museum.\\nJust weeks after it appeared to stall, Mr Palmer\\u2019s display of vintage vehicles worth more than $200 million is now set to be on show at a property west of Brisbane.\\nThe mining magnate pulled the pin on a planning application to build the ambitious project at his Palmer Coolum Resort on the Sunshine Coast in June after locals claimed it would be an \\u201ceyesore\\u201d.\\nInstead, he set his sights on a property near Lowood, a 90-minute drive from Brisbane.\\nThe local Somerset Council on Wednesday officially approved the project that will feature more than 1000 cars and 300 motorcycles.\\n\\u201cWe are hoping it provides a tourism boost for the region,\\u201d Somerset Mayor Jason Wendt told AAP.\\nMr Palmer is no stranger to bold ideas.\\nThe former politician was the owner of A-League club Gold Coast United for three seasons from 2009 before its licence was revoked following his running battle with the governing body.\\nAn artist\\u2019s impression of the proposed car museum at Palmer Coolum Resort, a plan that was ultimately scrapped.\\nHe also dabbled in tourism, scattering more than 150 replica dinosaurs next to his Coolum resort in a theme park dubbed \\u201cPalmersaurus\\u201d.\\nHailed as the \\u201cworld\\u2019s largest dinosaur park\\u201d, its drawcard was Jeff, a 10m animatronic T-rex that had a fiery extinction in 2015 when it burnt down due to an electrical fault.\\nThen there\\u2019s Titanic II.\\nThe one-time senator in March announced it was full steam ahead \\u2013 again \\u2013 for his plan to build the Titanic replica and recreate the doomed cruise, 11 years after first floating the idea.\\nMr Palmer is now all revved up to build the country\\u2019s biggest car museum following the council\\u2019s development application approval.\\nDo you have an opinion to share? Submit a Letter to the Editor at Sunshine Coast News via news@sunshinecoastnews.com.au.\\u00a0You must include your name and suburb.\\nThe Lowood site will feature 11 buildings for vehicle display along with 10 accommodation units, a cafe and a gift shop.\\nThe museum\\u2019s gross floor area is 43,000sq m, about the size of four NRL fields.\\nIt is set to eclipse South Australia\\u2019s National Motor Museum as the nation\\u2019s biggest car display.\\nThe project is expected to create about 80 jobs during construction \\u2013 which is set to start in 2025 \\u2013 and employ about 30 full-time staff.\\n\\u201cWe are excited about the opportunities this poses for the region,\\u201d Mr Wendt said.\\nHelp keep independent and fair Sunshine Coast news coming by subscribing to our FREE daily news feed. All it requires is your name and email at the bottom of this article.\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\nSubscribe to SCN\\u2019s Daily News\\n\\n\\nHiddenFirst Name(Required) Email(Required)\\n\\nEmailThis field is for validation purposes and should be left unchanged.\\n \\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\nGo backReturn Home\\n\\n\\n[scn_go_back_button]\\nReturn Home\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\nShare\\nFacebookLinkedinWhatsAppEmailCopy URL\\n\\n\\nShare\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n  \\n\\n\\n \\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\nOur Sister Publications\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\