ws Fax\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\nBreakingBusinessEntertainmentLife StyleSportsTechnologyKey Points from Day 2 of the R.N.C.: Republican Unity DisplayFacebookTwitterDiggReddItMixTumblrPrint\\nThe second night of the Republican National Convention was a display of unity within the party and the nation. Former rivals of Donald J. Trump, such as Nikki Haley, came forward to pledge their support. The Republican Party showcased confidence in its fate for the upcoming November elections by emphasizing an aggressive law-and-order message.Throughout the Trump era, there has been a divisive tone between the supporters of Mr. Trump and everyone else. However, the Make America Great Again movement inherently embodies unity, despite not being recognized by the news media and the Democratic Party elites. While the past strategy involved pitting members of the movement against others to secure a win, the current political climate seems to be shifting towards portraying Trumpism as a movement for all Americans, whether they realize it or not.Senator Marco Rubio of Florida closed the night by highlighting that Americans supporting the movement are not hateful or extreme. They simply desire good jobs, lower prices, secure borders, legal immigration, safety from criminals and terrorists, and a focus on domestic issues rather than foreign affairs. This message aimed to show the unifying aspects of the movement.The main theme of the night was unity, with a visual representation of loyalty. Former rivals of Mr. Trump, including Vivek Ramaswamy, Senator Ted Cruz, former Gov. Nikki Haley, Gov. Ron DeSantis, and Senator Marco Rubio, all expressed their allegiance to the former president. This display of support was a stark contrast to the tensions seen during the 2016 convention, particularly when Senator Cruz did not endorse Mr. Trump. This time, Mr. Cruz thanked God for protecting President Trump, which was met with a smile from the former president.The night showcased a united front within the Republican Party, highlighting the support and loyalty towards Donald J. Trump. The message of unity and common goals resonated throughout the event, emphasizing the importance of coming together for the upcoming elections. The Republican National Convention served as a platform to solidify the party\\u2019s stance on key issues and to demonstrate a unified front in the face of opposition.  TAGSConservative valuesDay 2Donald TrumpGOPHighlightsKey momentsMedia coveragePolitical analysisPolitical eventRepublican National ConventionRepublican partyRepublican Unity ShowRNCSpeechesUnity messageWireNews Editor SGAbout UsAdvertisePrivacyTerms of UseContact Us\\n\\u00a9 Wire News Fax     \\n\\n\\n\\n\",\n        \"type\": \"Document\"\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"lc\": 1,\n      \"type\": \"constructor\",\n      \"id\": [\n        \"langchain\",\n        \"schema\",\n        \"document\",\n        \"Document\"\n      ],\n      \"kwargs\": {\n        \"metadata\": {\n          \"source\": \"https://aussiedlerbote.de/en/the-killers-show-england-victory-and-then-cause-full-fan-ecstasy/\",\n          \"title\": \"The Killers display an England victory - and then cause full fan euphoria\",\n          \"language\": \"en\"\n        },\n        \"page_content\": \"\\n\\n\\n\\nThe Killers display an England victory - and then cause full fan euphoria\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n \\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\nSkip to content\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\nDark\\n\\nSearch\\n\\nen\\nde\\nes\\nfr\\nit\\npt\\ntr\\nru\\nro\\nold\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n \\n\\nSign In\\nSubscribe\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\nHot-Topics\\n\\n\\nPolitics\\n\\n\\nSociety\\n\\n\\nEconomy\\n\\n\\nSport\\n\\n\\nTechnology\\n\\n\\nHealth\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\nCulture \\u2014 News \\u2014 Ollie Watkins \\u2014 The Killers \\u2014 Netherlands \\u2014 England\\n\\nThe Killers show England victory - and then cause full fan ecstasy\\n\\n\\n\\n,\\u00a0\\n\\u00a0and\\u00a0\\nCarmen Simpson\\n \\n2024 July 11\\n . 8:24 AM\\n 2 min read \\n\\n\\n\\n\\ud835\\udd4f\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\nShare on Facebook\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\nShare on Pinterest\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\nShare on LinkedIn\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n Share on WhatsApp\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\nShare via Email\\n\\n\\n \\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\nBrandon Flowers of The Killers\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\nSemi-finals - The Killers show England victory - and then cause full fan ecstasyThe semifinal match between England and the Netherlands was a nail-biter on a Wednesday evening. The knockout game was a head-to-head race until just before the end, when Ollie Watkins, who had been substituted, rescued the Three Lions and their fans with the winning goal. Hundreds of kilometers away in Dortmund, The Killers were performing a concert in London.The Killers show England's semifinal win on stageAs numerous videos on X, formerly Twitter, show, the concertgoers didn't have to miss the game. The band showed the last minutes of the match, during which the English national team fought for a place in the final. The fans of the Rockband watched intently on a large screen. When Watkins' shot secured the EM-Final place, they cheered loudly \\u2013 and the Killers added to it.Without delay, they launched their biggest hit, \\\"Mr. Brightside\\\", in response to the jubilation of their and England's fans. The first notes of the worldwide hit were so recognizable that everyone in the hall knew what was coming next. The result: Complete ecstasy. Although \\\"Mr. Brightside\\\" originally deals with separation and hurt feelings, it has become one of the sing-along and party anthems in recent years.\\\"Today we played for England,\\\" the band wrote on X after the concert. \\\"It was absolutely brilliant. And football was a bonus, and 'Mr. Brightside' was the madness,\\\" an excited fan wrote.The English fans will have to tense up again on Sunday. They face Spain in the EM-Final in Berlin. And the Killers? They play the last concert of their Europe tour on Saturday \\u2013 coincidentally in Madrid.Ollie Watkins' winning goal during the semifinal match between England and the Netherlands was a highlight that even reached The Killers' concert in Dortmund. Despite being hundreds of kilometers away, fans watched the final minutes of the game on a large screen, cheering loudly as Watkins secured England's place in the EM-Final.After the goal, The Killers responded with their popular hit \\\"Mr. Brightside,\\\" which resonated with the jubilant crowd, despite the song's original theme of separation and hurt feelings.Read also:Caught up in the present: the end of \\\"The Crown\\\"Could a girl play every role despite her age not fitting the part?Through New Year's Eve with TV showsWhat's next for the series hits?\\n\\n\\nComments \\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\nRelated\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\nCulture\\n\\nSinger with stone on \\\"Walk of Fame\\\" honored\\nGelsenkirchen in Taylor-Swift-Fever: On the 'Walk of Fame' of the city, the singer temporarily has her own plaque.\\n\\n\\n,\\u00a0\\n\\u00a0and\\u00a0\\nKsenia Johnson\\n\\n\\n\\n2024 July 17\\n \\nPaid\\nMembers\\nPublic\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n \\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\nCulture\\n\\nEvery pendulum stroke costs 50 Euro: dealers bet rhythmically\\nBares for Rares - Every pendulum stroke costs 50 Euro: dealers bet rhythmically\\nDorothee Sudau and Liane Petersen from Hamburg brought a bracelet adorned with diamonds, named \\\"Bares fu\\u0308r Rares\\\", to the event. This heirloom was given to Sudau by her mother, but it had been hidden\\n\\n\\n,\\u00a0\\n\\u00a0and\\u00a0\\nAnne Legman\\n\\n\\n\\n2024 July 17\\n \\nPaid\\nMembers\\nPublic\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n \\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\nCulture\\n\\nFamily outing to his naval base\\nPrincess Leonor continues her training at the Spanish Navy. She was welcomed there by King Philip and Mum Letizia.\\n\\n\\n,\\u00a0\\n\\u00a0and\\u00a0\\nLauren Adams